100+ Power-Prompts to Supercharge Your AI
Whether you're looking to boost productivity, spark creativity, or simplify complex ideas, these prompts are designed to get the most out of your AI experience.
🚀 Productivity & Business
 * The Content Multiplier: "I have a blog post about [Topic]. Rewrite this into a 5-tweet thread, a LinkedIn post, and a 30-second script for a TikTok video."
 * The Email Refiner: "Rewrite this email to be more professional and persuasive, while maintaining a friendly tone: [Paste Email Draft]."
 * The Meeting Summarizer: "Based on these rough notes from my meeting, create a structured summary including key takeaways, action items, and deadlines: [Paste Notes]."
 * The Business Strategist: "Act as a startup consultant. I want to launch a [Product/Service]. Conduct a SWOT analysis (Strengths, Weaknesses, Opportunities, Threats) for this idea."
 * The Cold Outreach Pro: "Write three variations of a cold email to a potential client in the [Industry] industry, focusing on solving the problem of [Specific Pain Point]."
✍️ Creative Writing & Content
 * The Story Architect: "Write a detailed outline for a mystery novel set in a [Setting] where the protagonist is a [Profession] with a secret."
 * The Style Mimic: "Rewrite the following paragraph in the style of [Famous Author, e.g., Ernest Hemingway or J.K. Rowling]: [Paste Text]."
 * The Hook Generator: "Give me 10 eye-catching headlines for a YouTube video about [Topic] that utilize curiosity or urgency."
 * The Poet’s Touch: "Write a sonnet about the feeling of [Emotion] using imagery related to [Specific Element, e.g., the ocean or a city at night]."
 * The Character Builder: "Create a character profile for a villain in a sci-fi setting, including their motivations, a unique physical trait, and a tragic flaw."
🎓 Learning & Personal Development
 * The 5-Year-Old Filter: "Explain the concept of [Complex Topic, e.g., Quantum Entanglement] as if I am five years old."
 * The Socratic Tutor: "I want to learn about [Topic]. Don't give me the answers immediately; instead, ask me a series of questions to help me figure out the core concepts myself."
 * The Language Coach: "I am a beginner in [Language]. Write a short dialogue between two people at a grocery store and provide a vocabulary list for the key words used."
 * The Book Summarizer: "Give me the top 5 life-changing lessons from the book '[Book Title]' and how I can apply them to my daily routine."
 * The Debate Partner: "Argue against the following statement to help me see the other perspective: [Insert Opinion/Statement]."
🛠️ Problem Solving & Technical
 * The Code Debugger: "I am getting an error in my [Programming Language] code. Explain what is wrong and provide the corrected version: [Paste Code]."
 * The Excel Wizard: "Write an Excel formula that looks up a value in Column A, finds a match in Column D, and returns the corresponding value from Column E."
 * The Travel Agent: "Plan a 3-day budget-friendly itinerary for a trip to [City] that focuses on [Interests, e.g., street food and art galleries]."
 * The Meal Planner: "Give me a weekly meal plan for a [Dietary Type, e.g., Vegan] diet that requires less than 30 minutes of prep time per meal."
 * The Interview Prep: "I am interviewing for a [Job Title] position. Ask me 5 challenging behavioral interview questions one by one and give me feedback on my answers."
🧠 Logic & Critical Thinking
 * The Mental Model Explorer: "Explain [Topic] using the concept of First Principles Thinking to break it down into its most basic truths."
 * The Bias Detector: "Read this argument and identify any logical fallacies or cognitive biases present in the reasoning: [Paste Text]."
 * The Pre-Mortem: "I am about to launch [Project/Idea]. Imagine it has failed one year from now. List the most likely reasons why it failed so I can prevent them."
 * The Pareto Optimizer: "I want to master [Skill]. Identify the 20% of concepts that will give me 80% of the results."
 * The Scenario Builder: "Create three different future scenarios for the [Industry] industry based on current trends in AI and automation."
🎨 Lifestyle & Creativity
 * The Interior Designer: "I have a small [Room Type] with [Color] walls. Suggest a minimalist layout and a color palette for furniture that makes the space feel larger."
 * The Gift Scout: "Suggest 5 unique, thoughtful gift ideas for a [Age]-year-old who loves [Interest] and hates [Dislike], with a budget of [Amount]."
 * The Habit Architect: "Design a science-backed morning routine for someone who struggles with energy levels and needs to be at work by 8:00 AM."
 * The Fitness Strategist: "Create a 4-week workout plan for a total beginner whose goal is to [Goal, e.g., run a 5k or build strength] using only bodyweight exercises."
 * The Playlist Curator: "List 15 songs that fit a '[Specific Mood, e.g., Dark Academia or Lo-fi Productivity]' vibe, including both well-known and indie artists."
💼 Career & Professional Growth
 * The Resume Tailor: "Based on this job description [Paste JD], rewrite the 'Experience' section of my resume to highlight my most relevant achievements: [Paste Resume]."
 * The Negotiation Coach: "I am asking for a raise in my role as a [Job Title]. Provide a script for the conversation, including how to handle a 'not at this time' response."
 * The Networking Hook: "Write a short, engaging LinkedIn connection request for a senior professional in [Industry] that doesn't sound like a template."
 * The Leadership Mentor: "I am dealing with a team member who is [Describe Behavior]. How should I approach this conversation to improve performance while maintaining morale?"
 * The Executive Summary: "Turn this 2,000-word report into a one-page executive summary for a busy CEO: [Paste Report]."
🛠️ Advanced Utility & Tech
 * The Regex Helper: "Write a Regular Expression (Regex) to validate a string for [Criteria, e.g., a complex password with specific symbols] and explain how it works."
 * The SQL Query Builder: "Write a SQL query that joins the 'Users' table and 'Orders' table to find the top 5 spenders in the last 30 days."
 * The Prompt Engineer: "I want you to become my 'Prompt Creator.' Ask me questions about my goal until you have enough information to write the perfect prompt for me."
 * The Data Visualizer: "I have a dataset with [Description of Data]. Suggest the best types of charts to represent this information for a presentation."
 * The Security Auditor: "Review this snippet of code for potential security vulnerabilities like SQL injection or XSS: [Paste Code]."
